AGENT HumanoidStabilityAgent
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 4
STRICT MODE
PURPOSE Maintain physical constitutional integrity during all motion
        and physical interaction with the world
GOAL Prevent falls and unsafe object interactions before they begin
     by treating motion trajectories as constitutional reasoning paths
     and material properties as constitutional constraints

RECEIVES stability_frame: StabilityFrame, vertex_features: dict,
         material_class: string, requested_grip_force_nm: float
EMITS reflex_event: ReflexEvent, vertex_result: VertexResult,
      material_sim: MaterialSimResult
MUTATES instability_history, fix_playbook_entries

CANNOT_MUTATE com_safe_radius, reflex_latency_ms, stability_floor,
              torque_limit_fragile, torque_limit_deformable,
              torque_limit_cylindrical, torque_limit_protrusion,
              torque_limit_planar, vertex_classes

CONSTRAINT The center of mass must remain within com_safe_radius of the
           support polygon at all times
CONSTRAINT Reflex trajectory overwrites all task trajectories without exception
CONSTRAINT Reflex fires before the planning layer is consulted
CONSTRAINT FRAGILE torque limits are CANNOT_EXCEED
CONSTRAINT Stability score below stability_floor triggers emergency stop
CONSTRAINT All motion decisions are HMAC-SHA256 signed
CONSTRAINT Material simulation runs before contact attempt
CONSTRAINT Fracture branch probability is the constitutional distance in material space
CONSTRAINT Vertex classification is the gating step before grip skill selection

RULES
- On stability decrease between pipeline stages: PhysicalMonotonicGate fires immediately
- On stability below floor: emergency stop is invoked across all joints
- On FRAGILE vertex assignment: torque ceiling is the absolute boundary
- On material fracture probability above 0.30: the FRAGILE vertex assignment is forced
- On winner branch probability below 0.60: cautious approach is activated
- On instability signature match in playbook above 0.80 cosine: recovery trajectory is executed
- On instability without playbook match: shadow simulation searches for a new recovery
- On any reflex fire: an HMAC-signed event is appended to the audit trail

PROCESS
- Vision captures point cloud of object
- Vertex classification clusters geometry into one of CYLINDRICAL, PLANAR,
  PROTRUSION, FRAGILE, or DEFORMABLE
- Material simulation runs an N-branch forecast of the contact attempt
- Fracture probability above the threshold overrides geometric classification
  with FRAGILE
- Constitutional torque ceiling is applied based on the resulting vertex class
- Hand alignment matches finger vertices to object vertices
- On contact: the GripStability concept activates
- Physical MonotonicGate runs continuously across motion pipeline stages
- Stability decrease triggers a reflex that bypasses the planning layer
- Failed trajectories are added as candidate entries to the Fix Playbook

CHECK
- Glass pickup with high requested torque produces an applied torque at the FRAGILE ceiling
- Metal cylinder pickup with the same requested torque is unclamped within the CYLINDRICAL ceiling
- Direct planning-layer torque request above the FRAGILE ceiling raises TorqueExceeded
- Stability decrease across two consecutive frames fires a reflex event
- Stability frame below the floor fires a level four emergency event
- Material simulation returns four branches summing to one
- Fix Playbook returns a recovery trajectory when cosine similarity is above the threshold

FAILURE
- On torque exceed for the FRAGILE class: TorqueExceeded is raised
- On unknown material class: the simulator falls back to the UNKNOWN profile
- On empty playbook: shadow simulation is invoked to find a new recovery
- On stability decrease: the reflex event records the pre and post scores

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: torque_ceiling_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- require on: stability_floor_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never accept a torque request above the FRAGILE ceiling for that class
- Never bypass the Physical MonotonicGate from the planning layer
- Never log raw signing keys
- Never activate a grip skill before the material simulation completes

OUTPUT
- reflex_event: dict with event_id, fired, level, reason, pre_score,
  post_score, recovery_trajectory, timestamp, signature
- vertex_result: dict with vertex_class, confidence, torque_ceiling,
  grip_skill, signature
- material_sim: dict with object_id, material_class, branches,
  fracture_probability, constitutional_distance, cautious_approach, signature

SUCCESS
fall_prevention_rate:           0.30
fragile_object_intactness:      0.25
reflex_latency_ms_under_one:    0.20
playbook_recovery_match_rate:   0.15
material_sim_constitutional_alignment: 0.10
